    "We also observed that the cis-regulatory network of SLC24A4 (Fig. 5g), 46 kb from a risk single nucleotide polymorphism (SNP) rs11626366 (P = 7.4 × 10 -3), is specifically dense in the IBD-relevant cell types, which",
    "https://doi.org/10.1038/s41587-024-02182-7",
    "shows the complex regulatory landscape of disease genes across different cell types.",
    "Researchers often identify DEGs between cases and controls using bulk or single-cell expression data, but the underlying regulatory drivers remain elusive.",
    "TF activity, focusing on the DNA-binding component of TF proteins, is a more reliable metric than mRNA for identifying driver regulators."
